  <!-- Web Font Loading -->
  <!-- Webfonts should be treated as a progressive enhancement; our fallback fonts being the accessible baseline. -->
  <!-- However we need to take steps to ensure that accessibility, and that there is no FOIT -->
  <!-- While we await better support (esp mobile browsers) for native webfont-loading technologies such as font-display, we need a custom approach. -->
  <!-- Unfortunately, the Font Loading API does not yet have widespread browser support so we need to use a JS library like https://fontfaceobserver.com/ -->
  <!-- The current Sofrito Font Loadoing strategy is: FOUT with a class (https://www.zachleat.com/web/comprehensive-webfonts/#fout-class) -->

  <!-- Preload critical fonts. Works best with self-hosted fonts although can use with a font service too so long as the URL is stable. -->
